data.text:
UTAH: Earned four letters playing in 43 games with five starts ... played as a true freshman in 2007 before going on an LDS church mission ... returned to the team in 2010.

2012-Played in all 12 games with one start (USC) ... 4 receptions for 26 yards ... catches came against Northern Colorado, BYU, USC and Washington State ... honorable mention Pac-12 All-Academic team.

2011-Played in six games before suffering a season-ending knee injury against Pitt ... two starts (Montana State and Washington) ... even missing seven games, he finished third on the team with 22 receptions ... had 160 receiving yards and two touchdown catches ... career-high 56 yards on six catches against Washington, including a season-long 17-yard reception and a four-yard touchdown catch ... five catches for 46 yards against Montana State ... five receptions for 20 yards against Arizona State included a two-yard touchdown ... four catches for 32 yards vs. BYU ... was a member of the Student-Athlete Advisory Committee (SAAC).

2010-Played in 12 games with a start in the Las Vegas Bowl ... tied for first among the tight ends in catches (11) and finished second in receiving yards (167) ... his first reception since 2007 was for a touchdown against New Mexico ... 36-yard touchdown catch vs. San Jose State ... 29-yard reception to the 3-yard line set up the winning touchdown against BYU ... four catches for 49 yards at SDSU ... Academic all-MWC.

2007-True freshman played in all 13 games and started one ... seven receptions for 45 yards and a touchdown ... two catches for 17 yards at Louisville ... 12-yard grab for a touchdown against UCLA.

HIGH SCHOOL: Three-time first-team all-Sierra Valley Conference tight end/wide receiver ... third-team all-state as an all-purpose player in 2006 ... first-team all-Metro (Sacramento area) as a junior and senior ... all-San Joaquin Section in 2005-06 (he was the only junior selected in 2005) ... also played linebacker and was the league's 2006 Defensive MVP ... 2006 first-team all NorCal ... 62 receptions for 1,107 yards and seven touchdowns as a junior ... 61 catches for 1,033 yards and seven touchdowns as a senior ... lettered all four years in basketball and was a first-team all SVC selection as a sophomore and junior (currently in his senior season) ... 2006 Union Mine High School (Calif.) basketball MVP ... averaged 17 points, 6 rebounds, 4 assists and 2 steals as a sophomore, and 21 points, 9 rebounds, 7 assists and 3 steals as a junior.
